  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips (as finely as you can!)</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> red pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 500ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [900ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and add the <strong>saffron </strong>– this is your <strong>saffron stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper is beginning to soften, add the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>orzo pasta</strong> and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> saffron stock</strong>, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the orzo is cooked</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2208.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
